/api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/milestones/86", "html_url": "https://github.com/datalad/datalad/milestone/86", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/milestones/86/labels", "id": 6382960, "node_id": "MDk6TWlsZXN0b25lNjM4Mjk2MA==", "number": 86, "title": "0.15.0", "description": "", "creator": {"login": "yarikoptic", "id": 39889, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM5ODg5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/39889?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic", "html_url": "https://github.com/yarikoptic", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "open_issues": 0, "closed_issues": 22, "state": "open", "created_at": "2021-02-02T14:46:01Z", "updated_at": "2021-09-10T17:50:04Z", "due_on": null, "closed_at": null}, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2021-08-30T09:52:29Z", "updated_at": "2021-09-07T18:42:21Z", "closed_at": "2021-09-07T18:42:21Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "This core option claims that _any_ command can be submitted to a batch system. I think we should remove it from the API. Rational:\r\n\r\n- for most commands it makes no sense to submit them to a batch system\r\n- for those commands where submitting to a batch system is meaningful, there is not sufficient parameterization capability to work with anything other than NFS-style filesystem setups across the distributed resource\r\n- there is no support for prevent conflicting operations done to the datasets that are subject to a command, when submitted in  parallel\r\n- only a single system is \"supported\" (condor), and in the many years of datalad not a single one was added. I consider this an indication for under-use.\r\n- the name is suboptimal: PBS is a particular and ancient batch system, and not even supported\r\n- current implementation has little or no error handling (e.g. plain crash when `condor_submit` is not found\r\n- current implementation does not work on my test condor system (see log below)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Conclusion\r\n\r\nI cannot come up with a use case, where simply wrapping a (tuned) datalad command call into `condor_run` would not be superior to the `-pbs-runner` option use.\r\n\r\n```\r\n% datalad --pbs-runner condor siblings\r\nSubmitting job(s).\r\n1 job(s) submitted to cluster 613835.\r\n[INFO   ] Scheduled execution via condor.  Logs will be stored under /tmp/datalad-condor-ctzfh3d9.log \r\n\r\n...\r\n<long time passed, job long finished>\r\n% cat /tmp/datalad-condor-ctzfh3d9.log\r\ncat: /tmp/datalad-condor-ctzfh3d9.log: No such file or directory\r\n\r\n% condor_run datalad siblings -d $(pwd)\r\n.: here(?) [git]\r\n.: gh-ben(?) [git@github.com:bpoldrack/datalad.git (git)]\r\n.: gh-master(?) [git@github.com:datalad/datalad.git (git)]\r\n.: origin(?) [git@github.com:mih/datalad.git (git)]\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote the `-d` switch is only needed, because not all condor deployments put a job's PWD to be the submit PWD.", "closed_by": {"login": "yarikoptic", "id": 39889, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM5ODg5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/39889?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic", "html_url": "https://github.com/yarikoptic", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5938/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5938/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}